{"id":"9025","name":"Encode To Audio","tagline":"Converts video to audio","latest":"27787","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>![ETA](https://i.imgur.com/rMhKyBU.jpg</p>\n<p><strong>-How It Works-</strong></p>\n<p>Encode To Audio converts a video in your camera roll to an only audio file, using shortcuts \"Encode Media\" function. This allows to have conversion to be done on device, in a fraction of the time then sending it to your computer and back, and with a intuitive user interface.</p>\n<p><strong>-How To Use-</strong></p>\n<p>First you open the shortcut from your preferred method. Next, the shortcut will ask you for the file to convert, from Dropbox, the Files app, or your Photos, unless you have imported from Share Sheet. Once you have selected the file, you will be brought to the sharing menu, where you can save, share with others, copy to clipboard, of open in Quick View to hear what it converted.</p>\n<p><img alt=\"ETA\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/9vQ3oiu.jpg\"></p>\n<p>To import from Share Sheet, you would do it like any other action. Scroll down to the bottom and select \"Encode To Audio\"</p>\n<p><img alt=\"ETA\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/PiSFyPw.jpg\"></p>\n<p><strong>Note: This shortcut only works with video, and will not function properly if anything else is imported</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://routinehub.co/shortcut/1911\"><img alt=\"Graphics created with MediaKit\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/j1bSp3J.png\"></a></p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.321 - May 30, 2021, 3:15 p.m.</strong></p><p>Fixed bug that caused the shortcut to not work properly</p>"}